24. Employment termination benefits

Certain Turkish-based subsidiaries of the Group are required by local laws to pay termination beneﬁts to each employee who has completed one year of service and whose employment is terminated without due cause, is called up for military services, dies or who retires after completing 25 years of service (20 years for women) and reaches the retirement age (58 years for women and 60 years for men).

The termination benefits is calculated as one month gross salary for every employment year and as at 31 December 2017, the ceiling amount has been limited to TL4,732 (2016: TL4,297), approximately RM4,916 (2016: RM5,481). The reserve has been calculated by estimating the present value of future probable obligations of these subsidiaries arising from retirement. The calculation was based upon the retirement pay ceiling announced by the local government.
